Parliament, Monday, 04 March 2019 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations (SCOA) will tomorrow receive a briefing from National Treasury on the progress and expenditure of the Employment Creation Facilitation Fund (Jobs Fund). Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 05 March 2019
	Time: 10.00 
	Venue: Committee Room S35, First Floor, NCOP Building Meanwhile, the Portfolio Committee on Arts and Culture will receive a briefing from the Department on, amongst other things, the Ray Mhlaba project, Winnie Mandela House, the Mzansi Golden Economy and the missing R8 million from the Living Legends Fund. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 05 March 2019
	Time: 11.00 
	Venue: Committee Room E539, 5th floor, National Assembly ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS, MS YVONNE PHOSA, AND THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON ARTS AND CULTURE, MS XOLISWA TOM. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
